Jordan Hedges Jenna  and I just got the final achievement in Everlasting Summer.  It's a bizarre Russian dating sim that's free on Steam. The writing is .... well it has lines like, "I bit my lip until it bled" which should sum up the quality.  It makes up for that in creativity though. I'm talking Undertale levels of meta game story telling. It's absolutely worth checking out to explore all the endings.   It's also very well put together from a user experience perspective. You can easily fast forward through scenes you've completed already and it always stops the moment you start a scene you haven't played yet. So going back to try new possibilities is super easy.  There's also boobs. Plenty of boobs. Have fun!  EDIT:  I should mention, the Steam version removes said boobs, but the developers have a patch on their website that's super easy to install and restore the boobs.

description: Craig Hedges  added  3 new photos  ‚Äî with  Jenna Hedges  and  3 others . Thank you for all the wonderful birthday wishes, my friends and family. Not being particularly big on MY birthday celebration as the years go by, my usual drill the last few years is a day to myself at the spa, to rejuvenate, relax, reflect and contemplate the coming year. With Michael's birthday the day after mine, it is also a time to remember.  This year's birthday was really fun with a new chapter unfolding, being in business for myself and doing more of what I really enjoy. So I did break from the routine a bit, at Carol's insistence booked a Thai massage - OMG talk about stretching! And ended up suspended upside down in the aerial yoga class - it looked like too much fun but it was a workout - I pretty much sweated through my shirt by the end of that, good thing the Well & Being Spa has a cold dip... then yesterday breakfast at my favorite Matt's Big Breakfast with Teddy and the kids then we went to see Billy Elliott at the Phoenix Theater. Being on the front row for such an emotional show was intense - the music is so passionate and the cast was amazing, giving it their all for the final performance.   All in all, a nice sense of closure for 2016 and a great start to the new year. Blessings to you all.

description: Jordan Hedges  added  2 new photos . XCOM 2 UPDATE 1   Joseph Box 's character, Colorado Denverson, is progressing well as the team's newest ranger.   Gregory Bloom 's character, Gregaman, is incredibly prone to panicking but has otherwise proven resourceful.  My character, Jade MacBrady, is an unstoppable killing machine.   Michael Eickstaedt 's character, Alexandra McSnugglekins, has become the ultimate ninja. She's been incredibly handy for timed missions where I need someone to slip past the enemies and complete an objective.   Matthew Wray 's character, Kurt Hectic, is getting the hang of his new sniping gig.   Jenna 's character, A Pet Named Steve, is miraculously still kicking ass with no armor.   Michael Middleton 's character, Alexis Sanchez, now has an exo suit with a wrist-mounted rocket launcher.    Theo Hedges 's character, Lena Lethal, is a force of pure destruction.  I gave  Jackson  the right to customize a new soldier I got as a mission reward. His instructions were "Make him Vegeta."

Jordan Hedges Played a lot of XCOM 2 today.  UPDATE TIME!  The whole crew contributed to a special mission where the command ship was disabled and everyone had to defend the ship.   Matthew 's character, Kurt Hectic, completed his sniper training and went on his first mission. That mission was a rescue op to retrieve Arin Hanson, one of  Jenna 's characters who was captured a while ago.  I have way too many snipers.  Colorado Denverson,  Joseph Box 's character has completed his ranger training and will likely be on a mission soon.  I also had a bit of a panic because the Avatar Project meter, which can end the game once it's full, got filled!   I had 20 days to try and lower it so I put all my time and resources into making contact with a region close enough to an alien facility. Raiding facilities brings the meter down and thankfully the one I chose took it down by 2!  The adventure continues soon. I'll let you all know once it's time to start another random drawing for new character names.

description: Jordan Hedges Jenna  and I decided to give the CW D.C. Universe a chance and watched the episode where Darren Criss was supposed to play the Music Meister.  A Glee reunion (Gleeunion?) on a tv show where they're all super heroes?That sounded like a recipe for an amazing thing to watch. It wasn't. Here's why:  - Barely any singing. Darren Criss sang like two lines and the songs that were there were not great. How do you screw up an amazing idea like, "Two superheroes sing a song called I'm Your Super Friend" so BADLY.  - The Flash and Supergirl were transported to a dream world that was a musical. They weren't actually made to sing by the Music Meister.  - He wasn't even the Music Meister! He was just some alien that the Flash called the Music Meister as a nickname and the only reason they were transported to a musical world was because Barry Allen likes musicals, which as far as I can tell was established for the first time in this episode.  I feel like I need to watch the Music Meister episode of Batman Brave and the Bold to clean out my brain.

description: Jordan Hedges  added  11 new photos . Today's quest was a complete disaster.  The fishmen and other eldritch horrors of The Cove proved to be too much for the group of newcomers I sent.   Regina 's Man-At-Arms Duncan lost all hope early on.  Richard 's Antiquarian Ekene-Ata and the Abomination Eileen became irrational thanks to the fishmen that specifically inflict massive stress damage.   Jenna 's Houndmaster Brent rose to the challenge and became focused, but it was not enough to save his companions.  Both Eileen and Duncan fell to heart attacks.  With Ekene-Ata barely alive and half the party dead, I had no choice but to abandon the quest.  Brent is at the Brothel and Ekene-Ata is being flagellated at the Abbey, the only stress relief she'll partake in.  We will recover from this loss and press on. We're now at 3 out of the possible 16 deaths before this playthrough is over.  I'll be drawing names for our next two unlucky heroes in a moment.
